# NativeCore Framework - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
NativeCore is a zero-dependency TypeScript SPA framework. It uses native Web Components with
Shadow DOM, a custom History API router (with middleware, caching, prefetch, and route loaders),
reactive signals (useState, computed, effect, batch), lazy loading, JWT auth with a single-shell
architecture, GPU animation utilities, plugin API, a11y utilities, testing utilities, and
Puppeteer-based bot pre-rendering for SEO. No JSX, no virtual DOM, no React, no Vue.

## Critical Rules

### No Emojis
NEVER use emojis in code, console.logs, comments, or documentation. Plain text only.

### TypeScript & Imports
- Source: `src/**/*.ts` and `.nativecore/**/*.ts` — compiled to `dist/**/*.js`
- ALWAYS use `.js` extension in imports (ES modules requirement)
- Use path aliases; `@core-utils/` is for framework utilities, `@utils/` is for app utilities only
- Never import controllers at the top level — use local `lazyController()` in routes.ts
- `lazyController` is always defined locally in `routes.ts` — it is NOT imported from `@core/router.js`

```typescript
// Correct
import { Component } from '@core/component.js';
import { useState, computed, effect, batch } from '@core/state.js';
import { trackEvents, trackSubscriptions } from '@core-utils/events.js';
import { html, css, raw, sanitizeURL } from '@core-utils/templates.js';
import { dom } from '@core-utils/dom.js';
import api from '@services/api.service.js';

// Wrong
import { Component } from '@core/component';        // Missing .js
import { lazyController } from '@core/router.js';   // lazyController is local, not exported
```

## Path Aliases

```
@core/         → .nativecore/core/
@core-utils/   → .nativecore/utils/
@core-types/   → .nativecore/types/
@dev/          → .nativecore/dev/       (dev tools only — excluded from prod build)
@components/   → src/components/
@services/     → src/services/
@utils/        → src/utils/
@stores/       → src/stores/
@middleware/   → src/middleware/
@config/       → src/config/
@routes/       → src/routes/
@types/        → src/types/
@constants/    → src/constants/
```

## File Structure

```
.nativecore/                        # Framework internals — DO NOT MODIFY
├── core/
│   ├── component.ts                # Base Component class
│   ├── router.ts                   # SPA router with caching, prefetch, loaders
│   ├── state.ts                    # useState, computed, effect, batch, useSignal, createStore
│   ├── lazyComponents.ts           # Component registry + MutationObserver
│   ├── pageCleanupRegistry.ts      # Auto-cleanup safety net flushed by router on each nav
│   └── gpu-animation.ts            # GPU-accelerated animation utilities
├── utils/
│   ├── cacheBuster.ts              # JS module cache busting
│   ├── dom.ts                      # dom.query, dom.listen, dom.create, dom.within, etc.
│   ├── events.ts                   # trackEvents, trackSubscriptions, delegate, onClick, etc.
│   └── templates.ts                # html``, css``, escapeHTML, sanitizeURL, raw, unsafeHTML
└── types/
    └── global.d.ts

src/
├── app.ts                          # Entry point — keep minimal, no logic here
├── routes/routes.ts                # All route definitions + protectedRoutes export
├── components/
│   ├── core/                       # Layout components (app-header, app-sidebar, etc.)
│   ├── ui/                         # Your custom reusable components
│   ├── registry.ts                 # Lazy registry — add custom components here
│   ├── frameworkRegistry.ts        # Framework nc-* registrations (auto-managed)
│   ├── appRegistry.ts              # App layout component registrations
│   └── preloadRegistry.ts          # Critical components preloaded on startup
├── controllers/
│   ├── index.ts                    # Named exports for all controllers
│   └── *.controller.ts             # Page controllers
├── views/
│   ├── public/                     # HTML templates — no auth required
│   └── protected/                  # HTML templates — auth required
├── services/
│   ├── api.service.ts
│   ├── auth.service.ts
│   └── logger.service.ts
├── stores/
│   ├── appStore.ts                 # user, isLoading, error
│   └── uiStore.ts                  # sidebarOpen, theme, notifications
├── middleware/
│   └── auth.middleware.ts
├── utils/                          # App-specific utilities only
│   ├── form.ts                     # useForm helper
│   ├── formatters.ts               # formatCurrency, formatDate, formatNumber
│   ├── helpers.ts                  # debounce, throttle, generateId
│   └── validation.ts               # validateForm, isValidEmail
├── constants/                      # apiEndpoints, routePaths, storageKeys, errorMessages
├── types/global.d.ts
└── styles/
```

## Naming Conventions

| Artifact    | Format                        | Example                       |
|-------------|-------------------------------|-------------------------------|
| Component   | kebab-case (hyphen required)  | `user-card.ts`, `nc-button.ts`|
| Controller  | kebab-case.controller.ts      | `dashboard.controller.ts`     |
| View        | kebab-case.html               | `user-profile.html`           |
| Function    | camelCase + Controller suffix | `dashboardController`         |
| Store       | camelCase + Store             | `appStore`, `uiStore`         |

## Component Pattern

```typescript
import { Component, defineComponent } from '@core/component.js';
import { useState, computed } from '@core/state.js';
import type { State, ComputedState } from '@core/state.js';

export class MyComponent extends Component {
    static useShadowDOM = true; // REQUIRED on all UI components

    count: State<number>;
    doubled: ComputedState<number>;
    private _unwatchCount?: () => void;

    constructor() {
        super();
        this.count = useState(0);
        this.doubled = computed(() => this.count.value * 2);
    }

    template() {
        return `
            <style>.container { padding: 1rem; }</style>
            <div class="container">
                <span id="display">${this.count.value}</span>
                <button class="increment-btn">Increment</button>
            </div>
        `;
    }

    onMount() {
        // Event delegation on shadowRoot
        this.shadowRoot.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
            if ((e.target as HTMLElement).matches('.increment-btn')) {
                this.count.value++;
            }
        });

        // Option A: declarative bind (auto-cleaned on disconnect)
        this.bind(this.count, '#display');

        // Option B: manual watch
        this._unwatchCount = this.count.watch(val => {
            this.$('#display')!.textContent = String(val);
        });
    }

    onUnmount() {
        this._unwatchCount?.();
        this.doubled.dispose(); // MUST call to prevent memory leak
    }
}

defineComponent('my-component', MyComponent);
```

### Component API additions
- `this.$<T>(sel)` / `this.$$<T>(sel)` — shadowRoot-scoped queries
- `this.bind(state, selector, property?)` — reactive binding; auto-cleans on disconnect
- `this.bindAttr(state, selector, attrName)` — reactive attribute binding
- `this.bindAll({ '#sel': state })` — batch bindings
- `this.setState(partial)` — merge + re-render
- `this.patchState(partial)` — merge without re-render

## Controller Pattern

Every controller MUST return a cleanup function. Use `trackEvents` + `trackSubscriptions`.
Use `html` tagged template to auto-escape user data.

```typescript
import { trackEvents, trackSubscriptions } from '@core-utils/events.js';
import { html } from '@core-utils/templates.js';
import api from '@services/api.service.js';
import { store } from '@stores/appStore.js';

export async function myPageController(
    params: Record<string, string> = {},
    _state?: any,
    loaderData?: unknown
): Promise<() => void> {
    const events = trackEvents();
    const subs = trackSubscriptions();

    const data = await api.get('/endpoint');

    document.getElementById('container')!.innerHTML = html`
        <h1>Page</h1>
        <ul id="list"></ul>
        <button id="save-btn">Save</button>
    `;

    events.onClick('#save-btn', handleSave);
    events.delegate('#list', 'click', '.item', handleItemClick);
    events.on('#search', 'input', handleSearch);
    subs.watch(store.isLoading.watch(loading => toggleSpinner(loading)));

    return () => {
        events.cleanup();
        subs.cleanup();
    };
}
```

## Routing Pattern

```typescript
// src/routes/routes.ts
import { bustCache } from '@core-utils/cacheBuster.js';
import type { ControllerFunction } from '@core/router.js';

// Always define locally — NOT imported from @core/router.js
function lazyController(name: string, path: string): ControllerFunction {
    return async (...args: any[]) => {
        const m = await import(bustCache(path));
        return m[name](...args);
    };
}

export function registerRoutes(router: any): void {
    router
        .register('/', 'src/views/public/home.html',
            lazyController('homeController', '../controllers/home.controller.js'))
        .cache({ ttl: 300, revalidate: true })

        .register('/login', 'src/views/public/login.html',
            lazyController('loginController', '../controllers/login.controller.js'))

        .register('/dashboard', 'src/views/protected/dashboard.html',
            lazyController('dashboardController', '../controllers/dashboard.controller.js'))
        .cache({ ttl: 30, revalidate: true });
}

export const protectedRoutes = ['/dashboard'];
```

## Component Registry

```typescript
// src/components/registry.ts
componentRegistry.register('my-component', './ui/my-component.js');
// All UI components use './ui/' prefix
// Framework nc-* are in frameworkRegistry.ts — do not add them here
```

## State Management

```typescript
// useState
const count = useState(0);
count.value = 5;
count.set(prev => prev + 1);
const unsub = count.watch(v => {}); unsub(); // stop

// computed — MUST .dispose() in onUnmount
const total = computed(() => price.value * qty.value);
total.value; total.dispose();

// effect — re-runs when deps change
const stop = effect(() => { document.title = count.value.toString(); });
stop(); // dispose

// batch — one notification per subscriber for multiple writes
batch(() => { store.user.value = u; store.isLoading.value = false; });

// useSignal — SolidJS tuple pattern
const [getCount, setCount] = useSignal(0);

// createStates — batch create
const { name, age } = createStates({ name: '', age: 0 });

// createStore / getStore — named global store registry
const cartStore = createStore('cart', { items: [] });
const cart = getStore<CartState>('cart');

// Global stores
store.user.value / store.setUser(user)
store.isLoading.value / store.setLoading(bool)
store.error.value / store.setError(msg) / store.clearError()
uiStore.sidebarOpen.value / uiStore.toggleSidebar()
uiStore.setTheme('dark')
```

## Template Utilities

```typescript
import { html, css, raw, unsafeHTML, escapeHTML, sanitizeURL } from '@core-utils/templates.js';

// html`` auto-escapes all interpolated values (XSS safe)
const markup = html`<p>${userInput}</p>`;    // userInput is escaped
const trusted = html`<div>${raw(htmlString)}</div>`; // opt out of escaping

// sanitizeURL blocks javascript:, vbscript:, dangerous data: URIs
link.href = sanitizeURL(userProvidedUrl);
```

## DOM Utilities

```typescript
import { dom } from '@core-utils/dom.js';
// Also available as window.dom

dom.query('#btn') / dom.$('#btn')             // querySelector
dom.queryAll('.items') / dom.$$('.items')     // querySelectorAll
dom.within(parent, '.child')                  // scoped query
dom.withinAll(parent, '.children')            // scoped querySelectorAll
dom.create('div', { class: 'card' }, 'text') // createElement with attrs
dom.addClass / dom.removeClass / dom.toggleClass
dom.show / dom.hide
const off = dom.listen('#btn', 'click', handler, options?);
off(); // remove listener
```

## DO
- Return a cleanup function from every controller
- Use `trackEvents()` + `trackSubscriptions()` — never raw addEventListener in controllers
- Call `computed.dispose()` in `onUnmount`
- Use `html` tagged template for rendering user data
- Use `sanitizeURL` for user-provided URLs
- Use event delegation on `shadowRoot` in components
- Use generators (`make:component`, `make:view`) for scaffolding
- Use `.js` extension in all imports
- Use path aliases for cross-cutting imports
- Define `lazyController` locally in routes.ts

## DON'T
- Import controllers directly — use `lazyController()` in routes.ts
- Import `lazyController` from `@core/router.js` — it does not exist there
- Use `document.querySelector` in components — use `this.$()` or `this.shadowRoot.querySelector()`
- Forget `computed.dispose()` in `onUnmount` — memory leak
- Skip cleanup return from controllers — listeners accumulate across navigations
- Add logic to `app.ts` — routes go in `src/routes/routes.ts`
- Put `<style>` or `<script>` in view HTML files — markup only
- Forget `static useShadowDOM = true` on UI components
- Use emojis anywhere
- Modify files in `.nativecore/` or `node_modules/`

## Auth Pattern
- JWT tokens stored in `sessionStorage` (cleared when browser closes)
- Single HTML shell: `index.html`
- Protected routes listed in `protectedRoutes` export from `src/routes/routes.ts`
- Auth check: `auth.isAuthenticated()`, user: `auth.getUser()`

## Generator Commands
```bash
npm run make:component <name>    # Creates src/components/ui/<name>.ts + registers in registry.ts
npm run make:view <name>         # Creates view HTML + optional controller + updates routes.ts
npm run remove:component <name>  # Removes component + cleans registry
npm run remove:view <name>       # Removes view + controller + cleans routes
npm run compile                  # Compile TypeScript
npm run build                    # Production build
npm run build:bots               # Generate bot-optimized HTML for SEO
```
